Thailand Stocks: Banpu, Loxley, PTT Exploration, Sri Trang

-- B y   A n u c h i t   N g u y e n
-- 
2011-09-12T05:47:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-12/loxley-sino-thai-thai-union-thailand-equity-mover-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in  Thailand  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 12:30 p.m. break in
Bangkok.  The SET Index fell 18.96 points, or 1.8 percent, to
1,043.41, heading for the largest decrease in two weeks.  Oil companies:  PTT Pcl (PTT)  , Thailand’s biggest energy
company, dropped 1.9 percent to 315 baht, set for the lowest
close in two weeks.  PTT Exploration & Production Pcl (PTTEP)  ,
the nation’s only publicly traded oil explorer, lost 1.8 percent
to 160 baht.  Crude slid for a third day in  New York  as investors bet
demand for fuel may falter amid signs European policy makers are
struggling to contain the region’s debt crisis.  Rubber producers:  Sri Trang Agro-Industry Pcl (STA)  ,
Thailand’s biggest publicly traded rubber producer, fell 2
percent to 24.3 baht. Thai Rubber Latex Corporation (Thailand)
Pcl (TRUBB TB) decreased 1 percent to 3.96 baht.  Rubber futures in  Tokyo  dropped for a second day as the
sovereign-debt crisis in  Europe  raised concern that demand for
the commodity used for tires may weaken.  Banpu Pcl (BANPU)  , the biggest coal producer, slipped
1.3 percent to 626 baht. Banpu agreed to buy the shares it
doesn’t already own in Hunnu Coal Ltd., valuing the Australian
explorer at A$477 million ($495 million), the company said in a
regulatory filing to the Stock Exchange of Thailand.  Loxley Pcl (LOXLEY)  , a Thai trading company, dropped 2
percent to 3.92 baht. Investors are required to pay cash upfront
before placing orders to buy the company’s shares, the Stock
Exchange of Thailand said in a statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anuchit Nguyen in Bangkok at 
 anguyen@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at 
 dboey@bloomberg.net  